    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "The mobile phone preparation is available <b>without</b> a bracket for connecting mobile phones that support the handsfree profile (HFP) via Bluetooth®. When connected via HFP, PCM 3.1/CDR Plus serves merely as a hands-free system. Only the basic functions of the mobile phone can be operated using the PCM 3.1/CDR Plus. With this option, the GSM connection is via the mobile phone antenna. <br/>For more information on operation and the various functions available, refer to the “PCM” operating instructions. "
    
    }
    
    }
    ,
    
    {
    
    
    "type" :
    
    
    "static"
    ,
    
    "inputs" : {
    
    
    "para" :
    true,
    
    "html" :
    
    
    "If the vehicle is equipped with the optional voice control system (I-no. 671), the mobile phone preparation only has to be enabled and coded (Steps 1, 3 and 4). The part number 991.044.900.33 still has to be ordered so that you can request the required enabling code."
    
    }
    
    }
    
    ]
    
    }
    
